Exquisite. Made it for Thanksgiving and everyone loved it. Used Nabisco Famous Chocolate wafers for the crust. Used El Ray Bucare Dark Chocolate (58%) from Whole Foods for the filling layer and Valrhona 72% for the ganache glaze because I wanted the ganache layer to be darker, both in taste and color. Added 1 1/2 tablespoons of espresso powder to the filling as well. Doubled the ganache and used 2 tablespoons of warmed Kahlua in place of the water. I did a practice tart about a week before Thanksgiving and froze some of the slices from the trial run. Defrosted them in the refrigerator, and they were just as delicious. Served the tart with a raspberry sauce drizzle and a little whipped cream.

