O...M....G....I've made this 8 times now, and it's been an absolute eye-rolling hit each time. Some refinements that in my opinion make it perfect: 1) use a pate sucre crust, not chocolate grahams; 2) add a split vanilla bean to cream before heating; and 3) strain the filling into the crust. I use valhrona guanajo chocolate for the filling and perles for the glaze, then serve it with whipped cream sweetened lightly w/lavendar honey and a sprinkle of perles and raspberries.

